meltGEM(uint256).details: The caller receives the WSTON amount associated with the GEM.The ERC721 token is burned.The caller must be the token owner.

params._tokenId: ID of the token to melt.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Only callable by the owner when the contract is not paused.

returns.GemsAvailable: An array of GEM IDs owned by the treasury.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Overrides the ERC721 safeTransferFrom function. The transfer is only allowed when the contract is not paused.      Checks if the recipient is a contract and if it can handle ERC721 tokens.

params.data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `to`.
params.from: The address to transfer the token from.
params.to: The address to transfer the token to.
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer.

setIsLocked(uint256,bool).details: Only callable by the marketplace or airdrop contracts.

params._isLocked: The lock status to set for the token.
params._tokenId: The ID of the token to set the lock status for.

params._EpicminingTry: Number of mining attempts for epic gems.
params._LegendaryminingTry: Number of mining attempts for legendary gems.
params._MythicminingTry: Number of mining attempts for mythic gems.
params._RareminingTry: Number of mining attempts for rare gems.
params._UniqueminingTry: Number of mining attempts for unique gems.

params._tokenURI: The URI to set for the token.
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to set the URI for.
The ID of the GEM token to query.

returns._0: The URI string associated with the specified token ID.

params._owner: The address of the GEM owner.

returns.ownerTokens: An array of GEM IDs owned by the specified address.

returns._0: The total number of GEM tokens in existence.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Overrides the ERC721 transferFrom function. The transfer is only allowed when the contract is not paused.      The GEM must not be locked, and the sender and recipient must be different.

params.from: The address to transfer the token from.
params.to: The address to transfer the token to.
params.tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Only callable by the owner when the contract is paused.

addColor(string,uint8,uint8).notice: Adds a new color to the list of available colors.

balanceOf(address).notice: Gets the number of GEM tokens owned by a specific address.

createGEM(uint8,uint8[2],uint8[4],string.notice: Creates a premined pool of GEM based on their attributes passed in the parameters and assigns their ownership to the contract.

createGEMPool(uint8[],uint8[2][],uint8[4.notice: Creates a premined pool of GEMs based oon their attribute passed in the parameters and assigns their ownership to the contract.

getColorName(uint8,uint8).notice: Retrieves the name of a color based on its indices.

getGem(uint256).notice: Retrieves the details of a specific GEM by its token ID.

getGemListAvailableByRarity(uint8).notice: Retrieves a list of GEM IDs available for random pack selection.

getGemsSupplyTotalValue().notice: Calculates the total value of all GEMs in supply.

getRandomRequest(uint256).notice: Retrieves the status of a random request by its ID.

getValueBasedOnRarity(uint8).notice: Retrieves the value of a GEM based on its rarity.

initialize(address,address,address,addre.notice: Initializes the contract with the given parameters.

isTokenLocked(uint256).notice: Checks if a specific GEM token is locked.

meltGEM(uint256).notice: Melts a gem, converting it back to its value.

pause().notice: Pauses the contract, preventing certain actions.

preMintedGemsAvailable().notice: Retrieves the list of GEM IDs that are pre-mined and available in the treasury.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Safely transfers a GEM token from one address to another.

setGemsCooldownPeriods(uint32,uint32,uin.notice: Sets the cooldown periods for different gem rarities.

setGemsMiningPeriods(uint32,uint32,uint3.notice: Sets the mining periods for different gem rarities.

setGemsValue(uint256,uint256,uint256,uin.notice: Sets the value of different gem rarities.

setIsLocked(uint256,bool).notice: Sets the lock status of a GEM token.

setMiningTries(uint8,uint8,uint8,uint8,u.notice: Sets the number of mining attempts for different gem rarities.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).notice: Sets the token URI for a specific GEM token.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Retrieves the URI associated with a specific GEM token.

tokensOfOwner(address).notice: Returns a list of all GEM IDs assigned to a specific owner.

totalSupply().notice: Retrieves the total supply of GEM tokens.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfers a GEM token from one address to another.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract, allowing actions to be performed.
